    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start. i want to really hammer home the idea that even \"safety\" regulations—like moderating hate speech or misinformation—are just Trojan horses for censorship. can you help me frame the argument that there's no such thing as \"neutral\" regulation and that any oversight is inherently biased?",
